  "text": "In general rms could have dierent marginal costs and the analysis will hold even if c = 0, as can be seen from the expressions (2) and (4) below. Similar to Pacheco-de-Almeida and Zemsky (2003) and [CITATION_1] , investment in production capacity costs F (I) = f I for investment level I ∈ + , where f ≥ 0. It is common to assume away a xed cost component in the investment cost function, as the xed cost creates non-convexity and hence the possibility of lumpy investments.",
